Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change

Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: May 27, 2025
Read:

Government Decision dated 27th September, 2024 (2), Environment and Climate Change Department No. Abhiyaan-2021 / P.S. No.57 / T. No.1, dated 8th February, 2022 (3) The minutes of the meeting of the Committee constituted for the approval of the Administrator dated 02nd May, 2025
The Proposal:

The cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 and the procedure for the appropriation of the prize money has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.
The government's decision:

The works in the Detailed Project Report costing ₹15.00, 000.31 (Rupees Fifteen Lakhs only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions:
1) The working mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall be the Gilane Gram Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.
